    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1946-03-20T12:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1946-03-20T12:00:00-05:00" n="724"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d724">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">852.00/3–2046: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in France</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Caffery</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">top secret</hi>
                        <lb/>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">us urgent</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Paris</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1946-03-20T18:00:00+01:00"
                            >March 20, 1946—6 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received March 20—5:51 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1349. Department 1260, March 19. I handed our reply to Bidault on the Spanish
                    situation and brought out orally the points set out in Dept’s 1261, March 20
                        [<hi rend="italic">19</hi>]. He is very much perturbed because he does not
                    know what to do. He says he will do the best he can to avoid the issue [being?]
                    placed before the Security Council but Bogomolov<note n="54" xml:id="d724fn54"
                        >Alexander Efremovich Bogomolov, Soviet Ambassador in France.</note> has
                    been trying to see him for some days and he will be <pb facs="1077" n="1059"
                        xml:id="pg_1059"/> compelled to receive him within the next few days and he
                    is sure Bogomolov will press him for early Security Council action. He
                    pathetically asks for suggestions. Bidault is well aware that he has gotten
                    himself into a jam and is most anxious to get out of it.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Caffert</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
